  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">The analysis of heavy flavor lattice correlation functions to obtain insights into transport phenomena and bound state dissociation patterns is a difficult and interesting challenge from the point of view of lattice QCD spectroscopy. In this contribution to “Hard Probes 2015”, the recent developments and advances from different lattice efforts to determine the relevant spectral properties will be reviewed and discussed. The difficulties underlying this line of research will be highlighted and the obtained results assessed. Among others, results on the dissociation of charm systems and bottomonia, as well as the diffusion of heavy quarks will be addressed.</subfield>
